4:10 exhausted the smaller pool, causing new checkout\n      requests to fail while waiting for a connection. This resulted in a sustained wave of 500\n      responses until the pool size was reverted at 14:14.\n    </div>\n\n    <h2>Action Items</h2>\n    <ul class=\"actions\">\n      <li>Add automated alerting on database connection pool saturation to detect exhaustion before it causes customer-facing errors.</li>\n      <li>Require load testing against production-scale traffic for any change to connection pool or resource limit configuration before deploy.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <footer>Report generated 2026-07-12</footer>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2fce59fd-5c1c-4329-b994-6d1c46ebe15d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/Users/boeschj/Documents/GitHub/parchment/bench/.runs/2026-07-12T15-07-38-053Z/incident-report/html/rep-3","sessionId":"3ce1d4e0-d195-4585-a849-fc3bdb5fe47e","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"main"}
